commit.message:
Add support for Sercomm IP camera discovery. (#238)

Sercomm manufactures a line of wired and wireless IP video
cameras that are frequently rebranded and distributed as part
of a security package by vendors such as ADT or Comcast/Xfinity.

At this point they have been pretty well reverse-engineered as well
as rooted: https://github.com/edent/Sercomm-API

Add support for discovering enigma2 based devices (#241)

* Create enigma2.py

* Update enigma2.py

* Fix type issue failing build

* Fix mypi version

be more strict on songpal filtering (#240)

* be more strict on songpal filtering, skip devices containing bravia in the friendlyname

* rework filtering to be based on the available services

* use videoScreen instead of appControl, looks like SRS-ZR5 offers appControl
